leads.lead_text: Leaves glabrous; leaflets flattened, entire or slightly tridentate; sepals to 2 mm long, one-quarter to one-third as long as petals; petals deciduous; Corner Inlet area
Leaves glabrous to indumented; leaflets terete, or if flattened, narrow-cuneate with tridentate tips; sepals 2–3 mm long, (one-quarter to) half as long as petals; petals persistent
Leaves compound, petiole shorter than leaflets; central and eastern Victoria
Leaves simple or if trifoliolate petiole very much longer than leaflets; central Victoria
